<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO SERIES - DISASSEMBLE - STANDARD SHIFTER HOUSING (W/SUPER 10 ON COVER)
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="8">
        <title>STANDARD SHIFTER HOUSING (W/SUPER 10 ON COVER)</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If the two (2) sets of tension springs and balls from housing bores have not been removed,
                place the shifter housing on its side to remove them (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301776">Figure 76</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301776" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301776" filename="../figg13/G1301776.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 76. 2 Sets of Tension Springs</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the oil trough retaining bolts and oil trough.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With the housing rear to the right, lay the assembly on a flat surface (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301777">Figure 77</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301777" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301777" filename="../figg13/G1301777.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 77. Remove Shift Yoke</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">While removing the bottom yoke bar, remove the shift yoke (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301777">Figure 77</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">While removing the top yoke bar, remove the shift yoke assembly and block assembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301778">Figure 78</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301778" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301778" filename="../figg13/G1301778.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 78. Remove Shift Yoke Assembly</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the interlock pin (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301779">Figure 79</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301779" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301779" filename="../figg13/G1301779.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 79. Remove Interlock Pin</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Drive the center block roll pin out (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301780">Figure 80</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301780" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301780" filename="../figg13/G1301780.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 80. Center Block Roll Pin Out</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pull the center bar to the right and remove the shift select block (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301781">Figure 81</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301781" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301781" filename="../figg13/G1301781.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 81. Remove Shift Select Block</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the snap ring, washer, spring and plunger from the 1st &#38; reverse shift yoke (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301782">Figure 82</hotlnk>). Remove the plug, spring and plunger from the 3rd speed
                block (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301783">Figure 83</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301782" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301782" filename="../figg13/G1301782.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 82. Remove Snap Ring, Washer, Spring &#38; Plunger</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f1301783" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301783" filename="../figg13/G1301783.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 83. Remove Plug, Spring and Plunger</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the yoke or block parts; replace if necessary.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
